---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
import Lead from "../../components/Lead.astro";
import StepNav from "../../components/StepNav.astro";
import { url } from "../../lib/url";
---

<Base
  title="Meet the states"
  description="Step two: the everyday nervous system states — settled, fight-or-flight, shutdown, and the blends between them."
  crumbs={[
    { label: "start here", href: "start/" },
  ]}
>
  <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl">Meet the states, one at a time.</h1>
  <Lead>
    People describe a lot of what the nervous system does in terms of a few
    broad states. They're not boxes you're stuck in — think of them more like
    weather that moves through. Here are the main ones, in plain language.
  </Lead>

  <div class="prose">
    <h2>Settled</h2>
    <p>
      Safe enough. You can think, feel, connect, rest. Things aren't
      necessarily perfect — but there's room. This is the state most of the
      healing work is quietly aiming to make more available.
    </p>

    <h2>Activated (fight-or-flight)</h2>
    <p>
      Revved up. Anxious, urgent, irritable, on guard, hard to sit still.
      Energy is high and mobilized — the body is ready to do something about a
      threat, whether or not there's one to do something about.
    </p>

    <h2>Shut down</h2>
    <p>
      The other direction: flat, numb, foggy, heavy, checked-out. When
      fighting or fleeing didn't work or wasn't possible, the body can pull
      the plug to protect you. It's not laziness. It's a survival setting.
    </p>

    <h2>The blends — like "wired and tired"</h2>
    <p>
      Here's the part that's easy to miss: these aren't switches, they're
      more like dials, and more than one can be up at once. A very common
      blend is feeling <em>activated underneath and shut down on top</em> — anxious
      and exhausted at the same time. If that's the one that rings true, you're
      not broken, and you're far from alone.
    </p>
  </div>

  <p class="mt-4 max-w-[65ch]">
    There's a fuller version of this on the
    <a href={url("learn/meet-your-states/")}>Understand page</a>, whenever
    you want it.
  </p>

  <StepNav step={2} />
</Base>
